================================================================================
AI Fluency Framework attribution
================================================================================

Workprint's AI Fluency Evidence report section (src/workprint/ai_fluency.py)
and Playbook Worksheet export organize evidence under the competency names
and structure of Anthropic's AI Fluency Framework (Delegation, Description,
Discernment, Diligence), developed by Prof. Rick Dakan (Ringling College of
Art and Design) and Prof. Joseph Feller (University College Cork).

The framework and its own materials (course content, infographics, and
detailed definitions) are licensed separately under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0
(https://aifluencyframework.org/) and are not distributed as part of this
repository. Workprint restates the competencies' definitions in its own
words rather than reproducing the framework's materials verbatim, and
displays this same attribution at runtime wherever the AI Fluency Evidence
section appears. The Apache License above governs Workprint's own source
code; it does not grant any rights to the AI Fluency Framework's own
materials, which remain governed by their own CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 terms
regardless of how Workprint's code is licensed or reused. See
docs/foundation/DECISION_LOG.md, "AI Fluency Reporting Uses Anthropic's
Named Framework, With Attribution," for the full decision record.

